RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOMINUS TECUM pressed the pace from two wide to the head of the lane, engaged the pacesetter in upper stretch, dueled with that one to the wire and inched clear late. WYNN TRIP sped to the lead shortly from the gate, set a pressured pace the entire way, responded when challenged in the stretch and just could not hold off the winner in a game effort while second best. SWEET ANALYZER unhurried for the first quarter mile, made steady progress along the fence to the turn, angled out for an early bid turning for home and finished well to gain the show. HAUNTED HAZE stalked the pace from the rail through the turn and failed to mount a closing rally. B L'S CONCERTO chased the pace around the bend, raced wide down the lane and had no impact. PRESTIGIOUSLY WILD was never a threat racing one-paced throughout. BER CHER broke a step slow and trailed the field through the turn and showed late interest in the lane. IMAGINE DRAYGON was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, TRIAL OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At One Mile Or Over Since August 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this r ace on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.) (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: START SINGING pressed the pace from two wide all the way, took command in mid-stretch and finished in a determined drive to hold the closers at bay. GYPSY REWARD dropped back in the run down the backside, steadily gained through the turn while having to rally six wide at the top of the lane as the field fanned out and closed well to be gaining late. GYPSY WIFE was well placed tracking the leaders from mid-pack between horses into the far turn, and closed with a steady gain to garner the show. GOLDEN GOPHER stalked the pace from the fence down the backside, was hard held off heels into the turn lacking racing room, waited through the turn on the rail, tipped around the stopping pacesetter and came on again late in the drive. DESERT GLOW set a pressured pace the entire way, responded when called upon turning for home but weakened in deep stretch. FALL MOON trailed to upper stretch and showed some late interest in the lane. DEAR BEAU (IRE) well placed tracking the leaders and failed to mount a closing rally. CHICA BOOM was never a threat. ROYALS' LIL DIVA stalked the pace from two wide through the turn, made a bid turning for home and flattened out in the drive.

Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWAMPDRAINER reserved off the pace for the run to the far turn, commenced a long rally circling in the turn, wore the pacesetter down through the lane to be up in time. MY CALANTE unhurried for the first three quarters, was set down for the drive and finished well late in the drive to be gaining. KURT'S CHOICE broke alertly, set an early pressured pace, shook clear in the turn to open a daylight advantage and could not hold on late. FORTY STRANGERS stalked the pace from afar down the backside, narrowed that gap making a bid in the turn and failed to sustain that momentum. LITTLE RED RIFLE well placed to be in striking distance in the far turn and lacked a closing kick. SMART OXIE tracked the pace for a half and came up empty. SCARYATCANTERBURY rushed up from the outside post to duel on the lead, was set to a drive into the final bend and faltered. HALO'S LADDIE bobbled several strides from the gate, dropped back to be a distant trailer, was eased and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 8 7 1/2F Turf CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 a nd 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAIL TOWN took command from the gate, set a well rated pace while on a clear lead, responded when asked turning for home and remained clear never having been challenged. THREE ROUGH SHODS tracked the leader from the fence to the far turn, rallied up the rail cutting the corner and finished willingly to gain the place. FROSTED TEMPTATION prompted the pace down the backside, was set to an early drive midway on the turn and lacked a response. LUCKY'S LANE trailed most of the way and passed tiring rivals down the stretch. BURN BOSS chased from three wide down the backstretch mounting an early bid into the turn and flattened out. SCORE MCCOY broke a bit awkwardly to be at the back, made a wide middle move down the backside and dropped out entering the turn.
